709139f-a.text:

MAY B6 REPRODUCEL.
According to the New York Times of November 30, 1937, the Charles
S. Guggenheimer home (No. 923) will be remodelled for apartment use.
This edifice is the ornamented 5-story structure that adjoins the corner.
